{"name": "better-pyunit-format", "metadata": {"name": "Better-PyUnit-Format", "version": "0.2.3", "classifiers": [], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "A more readable text output for Python's built in unittest framework", "upload_time": 1725485576}, "documentation": ["# Better PyUnit Format\n#### A more readable text output for Python's built in unittest framework\n\n\n### Overview\n\nThis package provides an implementation of a test runner and a test result for the Python unittest package.\n\nThis package simply creates an override of the built-in TextTestRunner that removes all the formatting that\nit does by default and only runs the test suite. This means that this test runner passes all formatting\nresponsibility on to the test result. \n\nThe test result that this package provides formats the output of the test in a much more readable way to make\ninterpreting unit test results a bit easier for introductory students.\n\nThis package is targeted towards students and education and was built with that limited use case in mind. \nWith that said, please, feel free to use this in your applications and tell me what you think!\n\n### Using Better PyUnit Format\n\n1. Install the package via pip with `pip install Better-PyUnit-Format`\n2. Import the `BetterPyUnitTestRunner`\n3. Run your testsuite!\n\n\n### Example code\n\n```python\n# run.py\n\nimport unittest\nimport test\nfrom BetterPyUnitFormat import BetterPyUnitTestRunner\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    testSuite = unittest.loader.makeSuite(test.Test)\n    runner = BetterPyUnitTestRunner()\n    runner.run(testSuite)\n\n```\n\n### Example Execution\n\n```python\n# test.py\n\nimport unittest\n\n\nclass Test(unittest.TestCase):\n    def test_failure(self):\n        \"\"\"This test should fail\"\"\"\n        self.assertEquals(1, 2)\n\n    def test_success(self):\n        \"\"\"This test should pass\"\"\"\n        self.assertEquals(1, 1)\n\n    def test_error(self):\n        \"\"\"This test will error\"\"\"\n        0/0\n\n    @unittest.skip(\"Skipping this test :)\")\n    def test_skip(self):\n        \"\"\"This test will be skipped\"\"\"\n        self.assertEquals(1, 2)\n```\n```text\n\n====================\n--------------------\n[ RUN      ] This test will error (test.Test.test_error)\n[    ERROR ] This test will error\nA(n) ZeroDivisionError occurred:\n[ZeroDivisionError] division by zero\n\n-------------------- \n\n--------------------\n[ RUN      ] This test should fail (test.Test.test_failure)\n[     FAIL ] This test should fail\nFailure reason:\n1 != 2\n\n-------------------- \n\n--------------------\n[ RUN      ] This test will be skipped (test.Test.test_skip)\n[     SKIP ] This test will be skipped\nSkip Reason: Skipping this test :)\n-------------------- \n\n--------------------\n[ RUN      ] This test should pass (test.Test.test_success)\n[       OK ] This test should pass\n-------------------- \n\n====================\n[  FAILED  ] \n1 tests passed.\n1 tests failed.\n1 tests errored.\n1 tests skipped.\n1 / 4\n====================\n\n```\n\n### License\nThis package is licensed under the Unlicense. Feel free to use it for any purpose commercial or non-commercial.  \n"], "modules": [{"name": "BetterPyUnitFormat.BetterPyUnitTestRunner", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "BetterPyUnitFormat.BetterPyUnitTestRunner.BetterPyUnitTestRunner", "bases": ["TextTestRunner"], "methods": [{"name": "BetterPyUnitFormat.BetterPyUnitTestRunner.BetterPyUnitTestRunner.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "stream", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "descriptions", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "verbosity", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "failfast", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "buffer", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "resultclass", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "warnings", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "tb_locals", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "BetterPyUnitFormat.BetterPyUnitTestRunner.BetterPyUnitTestRunner.run", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "test", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["This function is adapted from the TextTestRunner in unittest.\nBasically, it is offloading all the result info to the results class and just serves as an actual runner."]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "BetterPyUnitFormat", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "BetterPyUnitFormat.BetterPyUnitFormatResult", "xref": {"fqname": "BetterPyUnitFormat.BetterPyUnitResult.BetterPyUnitFormatResult", "project": null}}, {"name": "BetterPyUnitFormat.BetterPyUnitTestRunner", "xref": {"fqname": "BetterPyUnitFormat.BetterPyUnitTestRunner.BetterPyUnitTestRunner", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "BetterPyUnitFormat.BetterPyUnitResult", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "BetterPyUnitFormat.BetterPyUnitResult.BetterPyUnitFormatResult", "bases": ["unittest.TestResult"], "methods": [{"name": "BetterPyUnitFormat.BetterPyUnitResult.BetterPyUnitFormatResult.printStatus", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "_statusMessage", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "_alignment", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "BetterPyUnitFormat.BetterPyUnitResult.BetterPyUnitFormatResult.startTestRun", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None",